<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Henry, Alexander. Travels in the Red River Department (Abridged), 1806. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0024</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">56</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">they were dragged out by main force.  Here we met some of our Young men who informed us that they had discovered the camp of the Schian<span class="AddHand-editors">[s]</span> at a small distance to the South &#8212; near the foot of a hill<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  This was agreeable News<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Each took his proper station<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The chiefs placed themselves in front.  The Colours were displayed &#8211; the Medicine stem occupied a conspicuous space.  We were placed in the Centre.  In this manner the procession went on Singing and shouting and rattling their <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Cheshequois</span> until we met a party of <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Schians</span> on horseback<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> Who received us very friendly but we did not understand their language<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Their horses were beautiful and maske<span class="AddHand-author">d</span> in a Curious manner &#8212; with artifi<span class="AddHand-author">cia</span>l horns in imitation of those of Buffaloes<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> While the Eyes and Mouth were trimmed with red cloth thus caparisoned they had a fierce appearance<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Advancing a little further we me<span class="DelHand-author">n</span><span class="AddHand-author">t</span> about one hundred men from the Camp <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Schians</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Sioux</span> and Buffaloe Indians all on horseback<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>heir great War Chief mounted upon a beautiful black Stallion rode full speed to the flag folded it in his arms then embraced the War Chief who held it.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[P]</span>assing on through the main body he selected some particular</p>
<p style="text-align:right;"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">persons</span>-</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[60]</span></p>

